titles: An elegie on the death of George Monck general of his Majesty's forces, Duke of Albmearale, &c. (As it was presented to the late, and most seserving duke his son.) Having appear'd about the same time an extraordinary starr.
author: Freeman, Thornburgh, b. 1648 or 9.
publisher: printed by and for Thomas Ratcliffe, and Thomas Daniel, and are to be sold at their house in New-street, betwixt Shooe-lane and Fetter-lane,
